<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id12279fd7-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1325"><num value="1325">§ 1325.</num><heading> Labor Statistics, Bureau of: report of Commissioner</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In addition to the usual number of the report of the Commissioner of Labor Statistics, twenty-five thousand copies shall be printed: five thousand for the Senate, ten thousand for the House of Representatives, and ten thousand for distribution by the Commissioner.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id12279fd8-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1269">82 Stat. 1269</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id12279fd9-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id12279fda-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 271 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s73">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 73</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/614">28 Stat. 614</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1913-03-04/ch141/s3">Mar. 4, 1913, ch. 141, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/37/737">37 Stat. 737</ref>).</p>
